-- Unilever Workers’ Union in U.K. Accepts Changes to Pension Plan
-- B y   Z i j i n g   W u
-- 2012-04-06T07:25:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/unilever-workers-union-in-u-k-accepts-changes-to-pension-plan.html
Unilever (ULVR) ’s U.K. manufacturing
workers’ union Usdaw voted to accept changes to the company’s
pension plans, ending a dispute which led to nationwide strikes
at the company, according to the union’s  website .  Usdaw represents workers at Unilever’s manufacturing
facilities in Wirral and Leeds, according to the website. It
also has a small number of members at Unilever’s research and
development units.  The union workers went on strike four days in December and
January.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zijing Wu in London at 
